Bruce L. Downey J.D.: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 4:40 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of NewSpring Capital



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Bruce L. Downey J.D.Partner, NewSpring CapitalAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships70--
Background

		Mr. Bruce L. Downey, J.D. is a Partner of NewSpring Capital since April, 2009. Mr. Downey joined NewSpring Capital on April 1, 2009 and is a part of the NewSpring Healthcare Team. Mr. Downey is Partner of NewSpring Health Capital II, L.P. Previously, he served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Teva Branded Pharmaceutical Products R&D, Inc. (also known as Barr Pharmaceuticals Inc.), from February 1994 to December 2008. Mr. Downey joined Barr Pharmaceuticals ... Inc. in 1993. He was an Interim President and an Interim Chief Operating Officer at Barr Pharmaceuticals Inc. since August 2007. He served as the President at Barr Laboratories Inc. from January 1993 to December 1999. Mr. Downey also served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Barr Laboratories Inc. of Barr Pharmaceuticals, Inc. He was a Capital Partner at Winston & Strawn LLP from 1981 to 1993 and a predecessor firm, Bishop, Cook, Purcell and Reynolds, which he founded in 1979. He began his legal career in the Honors Program at the United States Department of Justice. He worked as a Special Litigation Counsel at the United States Department of Energy. He is the Chairman of the Board of Ambassadors at the Johns Hopkins' Project RESTORE. Mr. Downey served as the Chairman of Generic Pharmaceutical Association, from 2006 to 2007. He has been an Independent Director at Cardinal Health, Inc. since August 2009. Mr. Downey  has been a Director at Momenta Pharmaceuticals Inc., since June 11, 2009. He serves as a Director at Acetylon Pharmaceuticals, Inc. and OncoPep, Inc. He serves as a Director of Putney, Inc. He served as a Member of the Board of Warner Chilcott PLC since 1997. He served on the Board of Editors of The Ohio State University Law Journal and was elected to the Order of the Coif. Mr. Downey received a J.D. from Ohio State University and a B.S. degree from Miami University in 1969.Read Full Background




Corporate Headquarters
